use str.length for arrays
use str.length() for string
char c = 'a' not "a"
use str.equals() for string for string content comparision: immutable
use str.equal()  for stringbuffer for string reference comparision: mutable
stringbuffer is thread safe
StringBuffer s1=new StringBuffer("rattaiah");
s1.append("addanki");//mutability
System.out.println(s1);

Unlie stringbuffer Stringbuilder is not Syncronised i.e thread safe hence multiple threads are allowed to operate on StringBuilder methods increasing performance


